import React from 'react'; import { Link } from 'react-router-dom'; import { Box, Typography, Button, Grid, Paper, Card, CardContent, CardMedia, CardActionArea } from '@mui/material'; import { ArrowForward, Code, School, Forum, MenuBook } from '@mui/icons-material'; const Home = () => { // Sample featured modules const featuredModules = [ { id: 1, title: 'Introduction to Verilog', description: 'Learn the basics of Verilog HDL and get started with digital design', image: 'https://via.placeholder.com/300x160?text=Verilog+Basics', level: 'Beginner' }, { id: 2, title: 'Combinational Circuits', description: 'Design and implement combinational logic circuits using Verilog', image: 'https://via.placeholder.com/300x160?text=Combinational+Circuits', level: 'Intermediate' }, { id: 3, title: 'Sequential Circuits', description: 'Learn about flip-flops, registers, and sequential logic design', image: 'https://via.placeholder.com/300x160?text=Sequential+Circuits', level: 'Intermediate' } ]; // Sample code example const codeExample = `module example( input a, b, output y ); assign y = a & b; endmodule`; return ( {/* Hero Section */} Verilog Learning Platform Master digital design with interactive Verilog lessons, exercises, and a supportive community {/* Features Section */} What We Offer Interactive Lessons Comprehensive modules covering everything from basic Verilog syntax to advanced design techniques. Live Code Editor Practice Verilog in a browser-based code editor with real-time syntax checking and simulation capabilities. Community Forum Connect with other learners, ask questions, and share your projects in our supportive community forum. {/* Featured Modules */} Featured Modules {featuredModules.map(module => ( {module.title} {module.level} {module.description} ))} {/* Try it out section */} Try It Yourself Simple AND Gate in Verilog This example demonstrates a basic AND gate implementation in Verilog. The module takes two inputs, a and b, and produces one output y. 
{codeExample}
 {/* Call to Action */} Ready to start your Verilog journey? Join thousands of students learning Verilog on our interactive platform. Create a free account to track your progress and join our community. ); }; export default Home;
